5table.html.body:
Table
For our last schematic, we'll add a table that has pagination and sorting built in.

Generate the table by running the following command. You can pass in any name for the component. We'll use 'table' for simplicity.
ng generate @angular/material:table 


We'll add table as the 3rd item in our nav list. Make the following changes

Add table route to the app-routing.module.ts
Update the router links and link name in navigation.component.html 


The table view is full width and is a little hard to see what's going on so let's add a little space to the view. In table.component.html find the top level div and add a class named 'table-container'. In table.component.scss, create a style for the class and set 'margin: 50px'.
table.component.htmltable.component.scss
  
    ...

    
    
  

  
  
.table-container {
  margin: 50px;
}

.full-width-table {
  width: 100%;
}



